article.headline: Wagner 100, Sacred Heart 93
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Teone Carroll scored 31 points, and Sean Munson and Courtney Pritchard each had 15 points as Wagner sent Sacred Heart to its fourth straight loss, 100-93 Monday night. Maurice Bailey led the Pioneers (12-15, 8-10 Northeast) with 32 points. Joey Henley added 16. Wagner (13-15, 10-8) started the second half with a 20-8 run, and led 81-56 with 6:40 left before Sacred Heart went on a 37-15 spurt to pull within 96-93 on a jumper by Justin James with 12 seconds remaining. Carroll made four free throws in the final 11 seconds to seal the win.
